Building with MinGW/MSYS:
    Build libmc--c:
    set HOME environment variable to your development home directory
    extract libmc--c to $HOME/
    cd libmc--c
    make
    make install
    
    Build test app:
    cd test
    make


Using:
    Copy "terrain.png" to $HOME/libmc--c/bin.
    Copy shared libraries to $HOME/libmc--c/bin:
        DevIL.dll
        ILU.dll
        ILUT.dll
        sfml-graphics.dll
        sfml-system.dll
        sfml-window.dll
        libgcc DLL
        libstdc++ DLL
        zlib1.dll
    
    cd $HOME/libmc--c/bin
    mc--c
    
    This test program will create a very small world, using terrain.png
    to draw the blocks.
    
Keyboard Controls:
    Forward             Up-arrow, W
    Back                Down-arrow, S
    Side-left           Left-arrow, A
    Side-right          Right-arrow, D
    Sink                X, Home
    Rise                Space, PageUp
    Toggle Mouselook    Right-click
    Turn left           End, Q
    Turn right          PageDown, E
    Return camera       Middle-click
    Tree color          R, G, B
    Quit                Esc

Mouse controls:
    Toggle Mouselook    Right-click
    Look around         Move mouse (mouselook)
    Forward/Back        Mousewheel
    Drag camera         Left-drag
    Return camera       Middle-click
    

Thanks to the following people who tested:
    vLK
